<CaseStudyLayout
  title="Aether"
  subtitle="Assessing social rhythm to surface mindful methods for mental wellbeing."
  category="Health & Wellness"
  year="2025"
  description="Aether — a social rhythm and mental health app by Mackenzie Hart"
  role="Product Designer"
  duration="12 weeks"
>
  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>
      Aether helps people understand how their social patterns affect their
      mental health. Drawing on social rhythm therapy — a clinical framework
      used to treat mood disorders — the app tracks the regularity of daily
      social routines and gently surfaces connections between pattern disruptions
      and emotional state.
    </p>
    <p>
      The core design challenge: make something clinically-grounded feel
      personal and approachable, not medical.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="callout">
    <p>"How might we surface the invisible relationship between routine and mood?"</p>
  </div>

